<P> The Community budget comes , in part , from the traditional own resources raised by the Member States ' customs services and therefore the principal role of Community legislation on guarantees and securities is to protect the financial interests of the Community .
<P> The defects in the procedures applicable to the security and guarantee system mean precisely that the corresponding Community revenue is not collected and has to be covered by additional GNP contributions from the Member States .
